ReportText: EXAM: CHEST RADIOGRAPHY EXAM DATE: 01/18/2021 05:38 AM. CLINICAL HISTORY: Acute respiratory failure. COMPARISON: XR CHEST AP PORTABLE 01/17/2021 5:55 AM. TECHNIQUE: 1 view. FINDINGS: Lungs/Pleura: Similar appearance of the multifocal airspace opacities and small layering pleural effusions. No pneumothorax. Mediastinum: Stable mild enlargement of the heart. Other: The endotracheal tube terminates 3.2 cm above the carina. The enteric tube courses below the diaphragm into the region of the stomach with tip off the confines of the film. Right upper extremity PICC tip terminates in the region of the right atrium. IMPRESSION: 1. Similar appearance of the multifocal airspace disease and small layering pleural effusions. 2. Right upper extremity PICC tip terminates in the region of the right atrium.
